<div id="descriptionContainer">
  
      <div id="description" class="readable stacked" style="right:0">
        
<span id="freeTextContainer8969993558469594088">An alternate cover edition of this ISBN can be found <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27841832-anil-s-ghost' rel='nofollow noopener'>here</a>.<br/><br/>With his first novel since the internationally acclaimed <b>The English Patient</b>, Booker Prize-winning author Michael Ondaatje gives us a work displaying all the richness of imagery and language and the piercing emotional truth that we have come to know as the hallmarks of his writing.<br/><br/><b>Anil’s Ghost</b> transports us to Sri L</span>
  <span id="freeText8969993558469594088" style="display:none">An alternate cover edition of this ISBN can be found <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27841832-anil-s-ghost" rel="nofollow noopener">here</a>.<br /><br />With his first novel since the internationally acclaimed <b>The English Patient</b>, Booker Prize-winning author Michael Ondaatje gives us a work displaying all the richness of imagery and language and the piercing emotional truth that we have come to know as the hallmarks of his writing.<br /><br /><b>Anil’s Ghost</b> transports us to Sri Lanka, a country steeped in centuries of tradition, now forced into the late twentieth century by the ravages of civil war. Into this maelstrom steps Anil Tissera, a young woman born in Sri Lanka, educated in England and America, who returns to her homeland as a forensic anthropologist sent by an international human rights group to discover the source of the organized campaigns of murder engulfing the island. What follows is a story about love, about family, about identity, about the unknown enemy, about the quest to unlock the hidden past–a story propelled by a riveting mystery. Unfolding against the deeply evocative background of Sri Lanka’s landscape and ancient civilization, <b>Anil’s Ghost</b> is a literary spellbinder–Michael Ondaatje’s most powerful novel yet.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8969993558469594088" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

