<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/699640-i-am-lost-trying-to-understand-the-last-2">I am lost trying to understand the last 2 sentences.
Does anyone understand it?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_699640'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F5942.Anil_s_Ghost">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/699640-i-am-lost-trying-to-understand-the-last-2">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/699640-i-am-lost-trying-to-understand-the-last-2">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1554988-ryan"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1253736189i/1554988._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1554988-ryan">Ryan</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I'm reading a hint of a darker take in there: Ananda is dying. -- I take those last pages to describe an attack on the village, the smells of the burn<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I'm reading a hint of a darker take in there: Ananda is dying. -- I take those last pages to describe an attack on the village, the smells of the burning grass, the petrol, and the grenade, the girl in the forest, and especially "The crack of noise as a layer of rock on his arm exfoliated in heat." Then the mention of the weather above the earth and Ananda briefly seeing this angle of the world (as he falls). He remembers that which was most important, before the boy touches him, concerned. In a world of such harsh touches, this last is the sweetest. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
