<div id="review_1177484491" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1177484491" />
    <a title="Erika" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23743588-erika"><img alt="Erika" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1439597923p2/23743588.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1177484491?book_show_action=true">Jan 22, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erika" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erika" href="/user/show/23743588-erika">Erika</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23743588-erika?shelf=books-read-in-2015">books-read-in-2015</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1177484491" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6632591064109732246">If I could give Anil&apos;s Ghost 3.5 stars, I would. <br/>On the plus side, much of the writing is stunning and Ondaatje creates images that will stay with me forever. One of the novel&apos;s central themes is the idea of stone, and everything it can symbolize. All the different ways of thinking about rock are woven brilliantly into the story and I came away feeling immersed in highly complex, satisfying metaphors. The book is also about the relationship we have with our pasts and the suffering caused by war.</span>
  <span id="freeText6632591064109732246" style="display:none">If I could give Anil's Ghost 3.5 stars, I would. <br />On the plus side, much of the writing is stunning and Ondaatje creates images that will stay with me forever. One of the novel's central themes is the idea of stone, and everything it can symbolize. All the different ways of thinking about rock are woven brilliantly into the story and I came away feeling immersed in highly complex, satisfying metaphors. The book is also about the relationship we have with our pasts and the suffering caused by war. <br />Yet while the novel's many gorgeous scenes are successfully strung together, there is still something missing. The writing is beautiful, but I rarely felt for the characters. And Ondaatje made weird choices when it came to leaving out certain important scenes, for example, two of the major characters are consumed with learning the identity of a skeleton they found, but when it's finally revealed, it's like, "Oh, by the way, he was this guy." <br />That's just one example among many. It's as if Ondaatje's plot-meter wasn't working. <br />Still, if you're a fan of his work, and I am, this is a worthwhile read.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6632591064109732246" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


